replies.bodyText:
if the client has no endpoint group registered, the URL can be resolved dynamically, if it does, we just send to the registered endpoint group changing the host header.

There can be more than one EndpointGroup involved here, so some kind of mapping is inevitable:
EndpointGroup groupA = ...;
EndpointGroup groupB = ...;

ArmeriaRetrofit.builder("https://group-a/")
               .endpointGroup(url -> {
                   switch(url.host()) {
                       case "group-a": return groupA;
                       case "group-b": return groupB;
                       default: Endpoint.of(url.host(), url.port());
                   }
               })
               .build();

service.fullUrl("https://group-b/foo");

